---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import siteConfig from '../data/site-config.json';
---
<BaseLayout title={`Privacy Policy — ${siteConfig.name}`} description="Privacy policy for Alex Rivera's portfolio website.">
  <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 pt-24 pb-16">
    <div class="bento-card !p-8">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2" style="color: var(--text);">
        <span class="gradient-text">Privacy Policy</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-sm mb-8" style="color: var(--muted);"><em>Last updated: March 15, 2026</em></p>

      <div class="prose-content">
        <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
        <p>This Privacy Policy explains how Alex Rivera ("we," "us," or "our") collects, uses, and protects information when you visit our portfolio website. We are committed to respecting your privacy and being transparent about our data practices.</p>

        <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>We collect minimal information necessary to operate this website. This may include basic analytics data such as page views, referral sources, browser type, and device information. If you contact us through the contact form, we collect the information you provide, including your name, email address, and message content.</p>

        <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>We use collected information to understand how visitors interact with the website, respond to inquiries submitted through the contact form, improve site performance and user experience, and maintain the security of the website.</p>

        <h2>4. Cookies</h2>
        <p>This website may use essential cookies for basic site functionality and theme preferences (such as dark mode settings). We do not use advertising or tracking cookies. You can control cookie preferences through your browser settings at any time.</p>

        <h2>5. Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>We may use third-party services for website hosting and analytics. These services have their own privacy policies governing how they handle data. We do not sell, trade, or transfer your personal information to third parties for marketing purposes.</p>

        <h2>6. Data Retention</h2>
        <p>Analytics data is retained in aggregated, anonymized form. Contact form submissions are retained for as long as necessary to respond to your inquiry and are then deleted. You may request deletion of your personal data at any time.</p>

        <h2>7. Your Rights</h2>
        <p>You have the right to access any personal data we hold about you, request correction or deletion of your personal data, opt out of any communications, and lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority if you believe your rights have been violated.</p>

        <h2>8. Security</h2>
        <p>We implement reasonable security measures to protect information transmitted through this website. However, no method of electronic transmission or storage is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.</p>

        <h2>9. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be posted on this page with an updated revision date. Your continued use of the website after changes are posted constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.</p>

        <h2>10. Contact</h2>
        <p>If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, please reach out through the <a href="/contact" style="color: var(--accent-violet);">contact page</a>.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .prose-content h2 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--text);
  }
  .prose-content p {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--muted);
  }
  .prose-content a {
    text-decoration: underline;
    transition: color 0.2s ease;
  }
  .prose-content a:hover {
    color: var(--accent-pink);
  }
</style>
